id: pmc-r9i0
title: Recommend pm merge reconcile (2026.7.22) over raw history-repair in Multi-agent merge safety docs
description: "pm-cli 2026.7.22 shipped GH-623 pm merge reconcile, a purpose-built audited post-merge reconciliation (preview via dry-run, apply with a message, then confirm with pm history --verify plus pm validate). Update the Multi-agent merge safety README section to recommend it over the blunt history-repair all-items primitive; link upstream MERGE_SAFETY guide. Fleet fan-out from canary pm-beads#42."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,docs,multi-agent
created_at: "2026-07-22T19:43:42.363Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T19:44:31.252Z"
deadline: "2026-08-31T00:00:00.000Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-22T19:44:31.252Z"
author: claude-opus-20260722
estimated_minutes: 15
acceptance_criteria: "README recommends pm merge reconcile with dry-run preview, apply, and pm history --verify plus pm validate confirmation; links upstream MERGE_SAFETY.md; CI green; PR bot-reviewed."
resolution: "Migrated the Multi-agent merge safety README recommendation to the audited pm merge reconcile workflow (dry-run preview, apply, verify) and linked upstream MERGE_SAFETY.md."
expected_result: "Agents merging concurrent branches are directed to pm merge reconcile, which re-greens pm history --verify + pm validate in one audited command with no data loss."
actual_result: README updated and CHANGELOG regenerated; reconcile workflow verified end-to-end under pm-cli 2026.7.22 on the canary.
